CHOOSING A LICENSE — QUICK GUIDE

  You ONLY need a commercial license if you want to:
    - Keep your modifications proprietary (not release source under AGPL)
    - Distribute or deploy a modified version without meeting AGPL-3.0's
      network-use source disclosure requirements
    - Otherwise avoid the copyleft obligations of AGPL-3.0

  You do NOT need a commercial license if you:
    - Use, modify, or redistribute under full AGPL-3.0 compliance
    - Run an unmodified version for any purpose (personal, internal, commercial)
      while making the source available as required by AGPL-3.0
    - Contribute modifications back under AGPL-3.0

If you are unsure which option applies to your situation, contact:
kykyglc@gmail.com
